Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["   Why a 3 x3 Jacobian?", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98584928584861*^9, 
  3.9858493020161266`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7ca01b92-90b9-674f-815f-\
3f61e106920c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Jacobian J of the forward kinematics links small joint - angle changes \
to small pose changes :\n   \n       \[CapitalDelta]pose \[TildeEqual] J \
\[CenterDot] \[CapitalDelta]\[Theta]\n\nSince FK has 3 outputs (x, y, \
\[CurlyPhi]) and 3 inputs (\[Theta]1, \[Theta]2, \[Theta]3), J is a 3*3 \
matrix whose (i, j) entry is ",
